o}/pulls/{number}/reviews`. A more robust approach would be to validate the URL format explicitly.\n- [PROMPT] The implementation uses `time.RFC3339` for the timestamp in the escalation final progress line (`retry 3/3:`), but the retry modify function uses a different format (`\"2006-01-02T15:04:05Z07:00\"`). This inconsistency could be confusing - the spec says RFC3339 for the escalation and the retry uses a different format for retry lines."}],"model":"MiniMax-M2.7-highspeed","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":79681,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":23387},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ff1960e9-a9a4-4d9f-bade-e958adcecf50","uuid":"55e58e86-3718-4c4a-be86-5758736d27e9"}
